## TL;DR

Assemble the `HintBundle` top-level type in `gbf-artifact` from the existing
`gbf-artifact::export_facts` and `gbf-artifact::preferences` modules (both
real), define the missing `BuildConstraints` third leg, and add
`EvidenceScope` consumed by `HintProvenanceInconsistent`. Schema only +
canonical-hash helper; provenance-validation logic owned by T-B2.9 / T-B2.17.

## Module placement

| Item | Path |
|------|------|
| Module body | `gbf-artifact/src/hint_bundle.rs` (new file) |
| Crate re-exports | `gbf-artifact/src/lib.rs` adds `pub mod hint_bundle;` and `pub use hint_bundle::*;` |
| Existing leverage | `gbf-artifact/src/export_facts.rs` (real), `gbf-artifact/src/preferences.rs` (real) |
| Tests | `gbf-artifact/tests/hint_bundle_round_trip.rs` (new file) |
| Builder helper | `gbf-test/src/hint_bundle.rs` (new file), exported via `gbf-test/src/lib.rs` |

`Cargo.toml`: ensure `gbf-policy` workspace dep on `gbf-artifact` (this bead
imports `CompileKnobId`, `CompileKnobPath`, `ConstraintValue` from
`gbf-policy`). Per the cross-edge T-B2.0d → T-B2.0, this dep is mandatory.

## Concrete type sketches

```rust
use gbf_foundation::{Hash256, EvidenceRef, ids::{LayerId, WorkloadId, TargetFamilyId}};
use gbf_policy::compile::{CompileKnobId, CompileKnobPath};
use gbf_artifact::export_facts::ExportFacts;
use gbf_artifact::preferences::CompilePreferences;
use gbf_artifact::lowerings::LoweringShardId;
use serde::{Deserialize, Serialize};

/// Top-level hint bundle carried alongside the artifact. Three legs:
///   * `facts`: measured ExportFacts (already real).
///   * `preferences`: soft compiler nudges (already real).
///   * `constraints`: hard build constraints (this bead defines them).
///
/// `compute_canonical_hash` returns the §2.4 domain-separated sha256 of the
/// bundle. T-B2.4 records this in `ValidatedInputHashes::hint_bundle_hash`.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]
pub struct HintBundle {
    pub facts: ExportFacts,
    pub preferences: CompilePreferences,
    pub constraints: BuildConstraints,
}

impl HintBundle {
    /// Domain-separated canonical hash. Prefix:
    ///
    /// ```text
    /// gbf:gbf-artifact:HintBundle:hint_bundle:1.0.0\0<canonical-json>
    /// ```
    ///
    /// Implementation may delegate to `gbf-report::canonical_json` if T-B2.2
    /// has landed; otherwise inline a small canonicalizer here and de-duplicate
    /// in a follow-up. The wire-protocol prefix string is normative.
    pub fn compute_canonical_hash(&self) -> Hash256 {
        // implementation TBD; see T-B2.2 for the canonical-JSON helper.
        unimplemented!("delegated to gbf-report::canonical_json once T-B2.2 lands")
    }
}

/// Hard build constraints. Each entry names a knob (or knob path), a value,
/// the evidence chain, and an `EvidenceScope` that bounds applicability.
/// Stage 0 class 8 (T-B2.9) emits `HintProvenanceInconsistent` when a
/// constraint references a scope outside the active artifact/workload/
/// target/lowering.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize, Default)]
#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]
pub struct BuildConstraints {
    pub entries: Vec<BuildConstraintEntry>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]
pub struct BuildConstraintEntry {
    pub knob: CompileKnobId,
    pub path: Option<CompileKnobPath>,
    pub value: ConstraintValue,
    pub evidence: Vec<EvidenceRef>,
    pub scope: EvidenceScope,
}

/// Typed value carrier mirroring `CompileKnobValues` shape from T-B2.0.
/// Constructed only as one of the listed variants; new variants must be
/// added in T-B2.0 first (CompileKnobValues source of truth) and then
/// surfaced here.
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(tag = "kind", deny_unknown_fields)]
pub enum ConstraintValue {
    PlacementProfile(PlacementProfile),
    BoundedU32 { value: u32 },
    BoundedI32 { value: i32 },
    BoundedQ8_8 { value: i32 },     // signed q8.8 fixed-point
    BoundedQ16_16 { value: i32 },   // signed q16.16 fixed-point
    Bool(bool),
    String(String),
}

// PlacementProfile lives in gbf-policy::compile (T-B2.0); imported by name.
use gbf_policy::compile::PlacementProfile;

/// Closed enum scoping a hint's applicability. T-B2.9 enforces the rule:
/// a fact may reference a *broader* scope than the build (e.g., all DMG
/// targets) but never a *narrower* one (e.g., a different model lineage).
#[derive(Debug, Clone, PartialEq, Eq, Hash, PartialOrd, Ord,
         Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(tag = "kind", deny_unknown_fields)]
pub enum EvidenceScope {
    WholeArtifact,
    LayerScoped { layer: LayerId },
    TargetFamily { family: TargetFamilyId },
    WorkloadScoped { workload: WorkloadId },
    LoweringScoped { shard: LoweringShardId },
}
```

## Serde / canonical-JSON discipline

(Same rules as siblings.) Plus:
- `BuildConstraints` derives `Default` so the empty bundle is constructible
  for tests.
- `compute_canonical_hash` MUST use the exact domain-separator prefix:
  `gbf:gbf-artifact:HintBundle:hint_bundle:1.0.0\0` (note the literal NUL
  byte before the canonical-JSON bytes).

## Canonical-hash computation rule (normative)

1. Serialize the `HintBundle` value to canonical JSON per RFC §2.5.
2. Concatenate domain separator + canonical bytes:
   ```text
   "gbf:gbf-artifact:HintBundle:hint_bundle:1.0.0\0" || <canonical-bytes>
   ```
3. sha256 over the concatenation. Wrap in `Hash256::from_bytes(...)`.

`HintBundle::compute_canonical_hash` MAY use `gbf-report::canonical_json` /
`compute_self_hash` if T-B2.2 has landed; otherwise inline. Either way, the
domain-separator string above is normative — round-trip tests assert it.

## gbf-test builder helper

In `gbf-test/src/hint_bundle.rs`:

```rust
use gbf_artifact::hint_bundle::*;
use gbf_artifact::export_facts::ExportFacts;
use gbf_artifact::preferences::CompilePreferences;

pub struct HintBundleBuilder { /* fields */ }

impl HintBundleBuilder {
    /// Empty: no facts, no preferences, no constraints. Canonical
    /// fixture for the happy-path Stage 0 test.
    pub fn empty() -> Self;

    pub fn with_facts(self, facts: ExportFacts) -> Self;
    pub fn with_preferences(self, preferences: CompilePreferences) -> Self;
    pub fn with_constraint(self, entry: BuildConstraintEntry) -> Self;
    pub fn build(self) -> HintBundle;
}

pub fn empty_hint_bundle_fixture() -> HintBundle {
    HintBundleBuilder::empty().build()
}

pub fn build_constraint_entry_fixture() -> BuildConstraintEntry { /* ... */ }
```

## Forward-compat boundary

- `EvidenceScope` is closed. Adding scopes requires RFC amendment.
- `ConstraintValue` is closed. New variants must be paired with new
  `CompileKnobValues` variants in T-B2.0 first; this file's enum shadows
  the source of truth.
- `BuildConstraints::entries` is `Vec<...>` — declaration order is part of
  identity (so the canonical hash is stable across reorderings only by
  intent).
- `HintBundle::compute_canonical_hash` cannot change its domain-separator
  string without a major version bump (`1.0.0` → `2.0.0` in the prefix).
  T-B2.4's `ValidatedInputHashes::hint_bundle_hash` would have to change
  in lockstep.

## Worked-example canonical JSON

Empty bundle (canonical fixture):

```json
{
  "constraints": { "entries": [] },
  "facts": { ... },
  "preferences": { ... }
}
```

(`facts` / `preferences` shapes are owned by their existing modules —
omitted for brevity.)

Bundle with one constraint:

```json
{
  "constraints": {
    "entries": [
      {
        "evidence": [],
        "knob": { "kind": "PlacementProfile" },
        "path": null,
        "scope": { "kind": "WholeArtifact" },
        "value": {
          "kind": "PlacementProfile",
          "PlacementProfile": { "kind": "Budgeted" }
        }
      }
    ]
  },
  "facts": { ... },
  "preferences": { ... }
}
```

## Why
RFC §7.3 class 8 (`HintProvenanceInconsistent`) and §7.5
`HintConsumptionSection`. T-B2.9 (provenance check) and T-B2.17 (consumption
record) both consume `HintBundle`. T-B2.4 `ValidatedInputHashes::hint_bundle_hash`
needs the canonical-hash helper. `ExportFacts` and `CompilePreferences`
already exist as real modules; the missing third leg is `BuildConstraints`
plus the assembled `HintBundle` top-level type.

## Inputs
- `gbf-foundation::{Hash256, EvidenceRef, ids::{LayerId, WorkloadId, TargetFamilyId}}`.
- `gbf-artifact::export_facts::ExportFacts` (real).
- `gbf-artifact::preferences::CompilePreferences` (real).
- `gbf-artifact::lowerings::LoweringShardId` (T-B2.0c).
- `gbf-policy::compile::{CompileKnobId, CompileKnobPath, PlacementProfile}` (T-B2.0).
- planv0 §"HintBundle is load-bearing" (~line 738).

## Outputs (deliverables)
1. `gbf-artifact/src/hint_bundle.rs` filled per type sketches.
2. `gbf-artifact/src/lib.rs` adds `pub mod hint_bundle;` and re-exports.
3. `HintBundle::compute_canonical_hash` implemented (delegates to
   `gbf-report::canonical_json` if available, else inline canonicalizer).
4. `gbf-test/src/hint_bundle.rs` builder + fixtures.
5. `gbf-artifact/tests/hint_bundle_round_trip.rs`.
6. clippy / fmt / tests pass.

## Pitfalls
- DO NOT alias `BuildConstraints` to `CompilePreferences`. Constraints are
  hard (can fail validation); preferences are soft (can be ignored).
  T-B2.17 treats them differently — alias would collapse the distinction.
- `EvidenceScope` is closed. Broader scopes (e.g., "all DMG targets") are
  acceptable; narrower scopes (e.g., a specific model lineage when the
  build is for a different lineage) are rejected by T-B2.9. The schema
  doesn't enforce this — T-B2.9 does.
- `compute_canonical_hash` MUST use the exact domain-separator string
  literally — including the embedded NUL byte. A regression test must
  pin the prefix.
- `ConstraintValue` is **shadow-coupled** to `CompileKnobValues` from
  T-B2.0. New `CompileKnobValues` variants must land in T-B2.0 first;
  THIS bead's enum then mirrors them. Diverging the two surfaces is a bug.
- `BuildConstraintEntry::path: Option<CompileKnobPath>` — `None` means
  "the whole knob", `Some(...)` means "a specific selector/field within
  the knob." Tests must cover both.

## Acceptance gates (cargo test names — at least these)

```
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::hint_bundle_round_trip_empty_fixture
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::hint_bundle_round_trip_with_constraint
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::build_constraints_round_trip
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::build_constraint_entry_round_trip
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::evidence_scope_round_trip_all_variants
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::constraint_value_round_trip_all_variants
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::hint_bundle_rejects_unknown_top_level_field
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::build_constraint_entry_rejects_unknown_field
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::evidence_scope_rejects_unknown_kind
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::constraint_value_rejects_unknown_kind
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::canonical_hash_uses_domain_separator
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::canonical_hash_changes_with_constraint
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::canonical_hash_byte_stable_for_empty_bundle
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::constraint_entries_preserve_declaration_order
gbf-artifact::hint_bundle::path_none_serializes_as_json_null
gbf-test::hint_bundle::builder_empty_matches_fixture_constant
gbf-test::hint_bundle::builder_supports_with_constraint_chaining
```

The `canonical_hash_uses_domain_separator` test must explicitly assert
the prefix string `gbf:gbf-artifact:HintBundle:hint_bundle:1.0.0\0` is
prepended. Suggested implementation: re-implement the hash by hand with
a literal prefix, compare against `compute_canonical_hash`. Equality
proves the helper uses the right prefix.

## Coordination notes

- `ConstraintValue` enum tracks `CompileKnobValues` from T-B2.0. Any
  amendment to the latter must add a paired variant here in the same RFC
  pass.
- `EvidenceScope::LoweringScoped { shard: LoweringShardId }` introduces a
  cross-crate dep on T-B2.0c. The dep is intentional: hints can scope to
  a specific lowering shard.
- T-B2.9 (provenance check) and T-B2.17 (consumption section) both
  consume this schema. Test fixtures from `gbf-test::hint_bundle::*`
  flow into both.

## Refs
- RFC §2.4 self-hash convention, §2.5 canonical JSON, §2.12 must-introduce,
  §2.14 schema absorption, §7.3 class 8, §7.5 HintConsumptionSection.
- planv0 §"HintBundle is load-bearing" (~line 738).
- Wave 0 in RFC §8.5.
- Depends on: T-B2.0 (`CompileKnobId`, `CompileKnobPath`, `PlacementProfile`,
  `ConstraintValue` source of truth), T-B2.0c (`LoweringShardId`).
- Blocks: T-B2.4 (`ValidatedInputHashes::hint_bundle_hash`),
  T-B2.9 (provenance check), T-B2.17 (consumption recorder).

