## T-A4.4: Interrupt-safe scaffolding for the BankLease ABI

**Target crate**: `gbf-runtime`
**Target file(s)**: `gbf-runtime/src/banking.rs`
**Reference**: `planv0.md` line 1583 ("ISR-reachable code/data live in Bank0, HRAM, or fixed WRAM only; no interrupt handler may depend on the currently selected switchable ROM or SRAM bank").

### Background

Interrupt handlers cannot depend on whatever bank happens to be active when the interrupt fires. Either (a) ISRs live entirely in Bank 0 / HRAM / fixed WRAM and never read switchable banks, or (b) the runtime saves+restores bank shadow state at IRQ entry/exit. We pick (a) per the engineering rules — it's the only clean option. This task scaffolds the *declarations* that ReachabilityValidation (Epic B) will later prove against.

### Implementation Notes

```rust
/// A section-privilege annotation that says "this section may not be reached by an ISR."
/// ReachabilityValidation enforces this later.
pub fn mark_isr_unreachable(section: &mut Section);

/// A section annotation that says "this section is ISR-reachable; it must be Bank0/HRAM/fixed-WRAM."
pub fn mark_isr_reachable(section: &mut Section);

pub struct InterruptSafety {
    pub kind: InterruptSafetyKind,
}

pub enum InterruptSafetyKind {
    /// Section runs with IF disabled; ok to depend on any state.
    InterruptDisabled,
    /// Section runs with IF enabled; must not depend on switchable bank.
    InterruptEnabledBank0Only,
    /// Section is itself an ISR.
    InterruptHandler,
}

/// Compile-time check: a section calling `emit_acquire_*` must be Privileged
/// AND not InterruptHandler.
pub fn check_lease_emission_legal(section: &Section) -> Result<(), BankAbiViolation>;
```

This task does NOT implement the ReachabilityValidation pass — that's Epic B Stage 12 sub-pass. What it does is provide the *annotations* and *local checks* that the pass will later globally validate.

### Acceptance Criteria

```bash
cargo check -p gbf-runtime
cargo test -p gbf-runtime -- banking::isr_section_cannot_lease    # ISR section calling emit_acquire_* fails check_lease_emission_legal
cargo test -p gbf-runtime -- banking::privileged_section_can_lease # Privileged + non-ISR section passes
cargo test -p gbf-runtime -- banking::annotations_serializable     # Annotations survive serialization for later passes
```

### Constitution Checkpoints

- §I.1: BankAbiViolation enumerates exact failure cases.
- §III.1: ISR/lease conflicts caught at compile-time where possible, with whole-program ReachabilityValidation as the fallback.

