## Review Correction

I agree with the review that bd-ubm's closure over-assigned the router/expert differentiable Burn path to bd-1mv. bd-1mv was already closed and only covers the generic Burn adapter layer plus existing ternary/activation/norm adapter support.

Corrected ownership:
- bd-1ptv now owns Top1RouterQat and ExpertBlockQat Burn adapters.
- bd-2uw remains the owner for full F4 Off/Soft/Hard per-phase QAT hardness control.
- bd-1b3 remains the owner for the standard batch/token router z-loss and load-balance training losses.
- bd-122 remains the owner for contiguous-window temporal smoothness policy.

Code follow-up applied in this patch:
- router mutable forward now rejects non-finite computed activations/logits/probabilities/losses before advancing temporal state;
- router temporal state now stores the previous soft routing distribution, not hard dispatch weights;
- RouterAuxLosses now names its per-token balancing term as a token balance proxy, leaving the standard batch loss to bd-1b3;
- SharedDenseBranch now receives the caller's activation phase mode instead of forcing Train mode;
- top-1 ties now choose the lowest expert index deterministically, and the default rank clamp is documented for tiny expert sets.
